Suspected gunmen on Wednesday killed two persons and injured at least two others at the Internally Displaced Persons(IDPs) camp in Rantis community of Gashish District I Barkin Ladi Local Government Area of Plateau State. It was gathered the IDPs were rebuilding their resettlement homes when the attack occurred. It was learnt the gunmen, numbering six, stormed the camp on three motorcycles and shot sporadically around 3:40pm. The IDPs were said to have completed work for the day and were about leaving the site when the gunmen showed up. Two of them, Dalyop Boyi and Gyang Jugu, were killed while three others, including Pastor Samson Boyi, Dahwol Jam and Pam Boyi sustained gunshot injuries. The Nation learnt the gunmen also burnt a Volkswagon Vento belonging to one of the deceased, Dalyop Boyi.   Journalists launch book on experiences of campus reporters     VC seeks support to reposition varsity     Council donates 150 jamb forms   Over 200 persons were killed and property worth millions destroyed with over 17,000 displaced in June, 2018 when some communities in Barkin Ladi and Riyom Local Government Areas of Plateau State were attacked. Vice President Yemi Osinbajo had assured the communities N10bnwould be released by the Federal Government through the State Government to bring relief and succour to the people. The Nation learnt the Federal government was yet to redeem the pledge. Osinbajo had also promised a permanent Mobile Police Squadron will be stationed in Gashish to improve security of the area. Plateau police spokesman ASP Gabriel Ogaba confirmed the attack to The Nation. He said: “We are aware of the attack at th IDP camp by unknown gunmen, two people were killed, two injured. Police deployment has been carried out, while investigation is ongoing.”